def gcc(sig, refsig, method="PHAT", interp=1):

    assert method in ["PHAT", "CC"]
    
    n = sig.shape[0] + refsig.shape[0]
    
    SIG = np.fft.rfft(sig, n=n)         
    REFSIG = np.fft.rfft(refsig, n=n)
    R = SIG * np.conj(REFSIG)
    
    if method == "PHAT":
        ccf = np.fft.irfft(R / np.abs(R), n=(interp * n)) # discard the ampltude and keep the phase
    elif method == "CC":
        ccf = np.fft.irfft(R, n=(interp * n))             # standard cross-correlation
    
    max_shift = int(interp * n / 2)

    ccf = np.concatenate((ccf[-max_shift:], ccf[:max_shift+1]))

    shift = np.argmax(np.abs(ccf)) - max_shift
    return shift, ccf, max_shift

def gcc_phat(sig, refsig):
    return gcc(sig, refsig, method="PHAT")

def get_topK(top_k, arr):
    top_k_idx=arr.argsort()[::-1][0:top_k]
    return top_k_idx

1. Read Audios¶

  • We play two sources, 0 and 1, simoutineously.
  • To obtain the TOAs of LOS and ECHO of each source, we insert pseudo-random white noise immediately proceeding each source.

import IPython

interp=1 

fs = 48000
frame = np.load('./frame.npy')

subframes = []
for i in range(4):   #  4 audio channels
    subframes.append(frame[i::8])


print("Click to play the audio: (To change the channel, switch the index (0, 1, 2, 3) of subframes):")
IPython.display.Audio(subframes[0], rate=fs)

2. For each audio channel, we extract the ToAs of LOS and ECHO of source 0 from it.¶

In [4]:
%matplotlib inline

fs = 48000
np.random.seed(0)
awgn0 = np.random.randn(int(0.1*fs))  # PN noise played by source 0 




s0_los_idxs = []  # LOS index of source 0
s0_echo_idxs = [] # ECHO index of source 0




for i in range(4):
    
    # convolve channel i with the awgn0 to detect LOS and ECHO
    cor = signal.fftconvolve(subframes[i], awgn0[::-1])
    cor = abs(cor)
    cor = cor / np.max(cor)

    
    # find LOS and ECHO indexs
    peak_idxs, _ = signal.find_peaks(cor, height=np.max(cor)*0.55, distance=15) 
    
    
    
    
    #plot LOS and ECHO paths.
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,3))
    plt.plot(cor, color="#4d4d4d")
    plt.plot(peak_idxs[0], cor[peak_idxs[0]], "o", color="red", ms=10, label="LOS of Source 0")
    plt.plot(peak_idxs[1], cor[peak_idxs[1]], "x", color="red", ms=10, label="ECHO of Source 0")
    
    plt.title("Mic. " + str(i), fontsize=fontsize)
    plt.xlim([peak_idxs[0]-100, peak_idxs[0]+ 3000])
    plt.xlabel("Index [sample]", fontsize=fontsize)
    plt.xticks( fontsize=fontsize)
    plt.ylabel("CIR", fontsize=fontsize)
    plt.yticks( fontsize=fontsize)
    plt.legend(fontsize=fontsize)
    
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig("./figures/source0_"+"mic_" + str(i) + ".jpg")
    
    #save the ground truth
    s0_los_idxs.append(peak_idxs[0])
    s0_echo_idxs.append(peak_idxs[1])
    
    
    
    
    #remove awgn0 from the audio,  since awgn0 is not supposed to exist in practice
    subframes[i][peak_idxs[0] -int(0.1*fs):peak_idxs[0]+int(0.3*fs)] = 0

for i in range(4):

    cor = signal.fftconvolve(subframes[i], awgn1[::-1]) #
    cor = abs(cor)
    cor = cor / np.max(cor)
        
    # find LOS and ECHO indexs
    peak_idxs, properties = signal.find_peaks(cor, height=np.max(cor)*0.55, distance=15)
    
    #plot LOS and ECHO paths.
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,3))
    plt.plot(cor, color="#4d4d4d")

    plt.yticks( fontsize=fontsize)

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig("./figures/source1_"+"mic_" + str(i) + ".jpg")

    subframes[i][peak_idxs[0] -int(0.1*fs):peak_idxs[0]+int(0.3*fs)] = 0
